(486, 3,N'Bioshock 2 definitely doesnt do everything better than the first game, but I actually still enjoy it ever so slightly more. The guns are better, playing as a Big Daddy and using the drill is awesome, you can use weapons and plasmids at the same time, and the entire plasmid system is expanded upon pretty massively to the point where you become insanely overpowered. Basically, everything gameplay related, especially combat, is improved upon significantly. It has a bit of a slow start, and some of the changes are a little awkward to get used to at first, but it only gets better as it progresses. Better to have that than be like the first game and hit its peak too early.',N'2024-10-21'),
