(693, 7,N'I had a phenomenal time with this, but Im not sure I ever want to see a game play like this again. By making the combat a puzzle process, the points where I stopped playing were literally gated by no longer being able to see the solutions to the puzzles and doing poorly in combat as a result. Its wild that an RPGs combat could become so mentally taxing that I had to stop for the night and go to bed, to clear my head. A really unusual experience. Also the story is pretty cute. That helped.',N'2024-03-09'),
